The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Feb. 1: Real estate company DLF Universal has entered into a joint venture with UK-based Laing ORourke for infrastructure projects. The new entity will take off with an initial investment of Rs 500 crore. ?We have formed a 50:50 JV company, DLF Laing ORourke, which will make an initial investment of close to Rs 500 crore,? said DLF vice-chairman Rajiv Singh. Both partners will contribute Rs 250 crore each towards the initial corpus, he added. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 1: The National Pharmaceutical Pricing Authority today increased the price of metronidazole benzoate from Rs 373 per kg to Rs 401 per kg. The drug is used for the treatment of amoebic infection.

 New Delhi, Feb. 1: Petroleum minister Murli Deora has sought a reduction in customs duty on crude oil and specific duty on products to stem the losses incurred by navratna PSUs this fiscal.

 New Delhi, Feb. 1: British insurer Aviva Plc has acquired 51 per cent in Sri Lanka?s Eagle Insurance Ltd for ?15 million. It has also entered into a bancassurance tieup with NDB bank, the emerald island?s biggest bank.

 Mumbai, Feb. 1: Tata Consultancy Services Ltd today said it has merged three subsidiaries ? Airline Financial Services Ltd, TCS Business Transformation Solutions Ltd and Aviation Software Development Consultancy Ltd ? with itself.




